genresAdvancedInfo.name: guam indie
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Guam indie is a music genre that originated in Guam, a U.S. territory located in the Western Pacific Ocean. The genre is characterized by its use of island rhythms, reggae influences, and catchy melodies. Guam indie bands often sing in Chamorro, the native language of Guam, and incorporate traditional instruments such as the ukulele and guitar. The genre has a vibrant and growing music scene and has produced some notable artists.
